# Cursor rules ‚Äî tableau-fabric-skills

Rules for Cursor working in this repository. The complete agent guide is `AGENTS.md`; the
non-negotiable rules are repeated here.

## Install / consume (for agents)

To make these skills actually load in a client, register the **plugin** -- do NOT copy folders
into `~/.copilot/skills/` (current GitHub Copilot CLI does not auto-scan it):

```
/plugin marketplace add Yarbrdab000/tableau-fabric-skills
/plugin install tableau-fabric-skills@tableau-collection
```

Start a new session, then verify with `/plugin list` and `/skills list`. Full details /
uninstall: `INSTALL.md` / `UNINSTALL.md`.

## Project

`tableau-fabric-skills` ‚Äî a standalone collection of three Tableau -> Microsoft Fabric / Power BI
agent skills (`tableau-datasource-profiler`, `tableau-mcp-landing-zone`, `tableau-migration`).
Canonical sources live in `skills/<name>/`; byte-identical mirror copies live in
`plugins/tableau-fabric-skills/skills/<name>/`.

## Must-follow rules

- Environment: Windows PowerShell. Do not use PowerShell 7-only syntax (`&&`, `||`, `??`, `?.`)
  and do not rely on heredocs (write a temp file instead). Use `py -3.11` (a bare `py` lacks
  pytest). Read BOM files as `utf-8-sig`; write JSON manifests as UTF-8 without a BOM.
- Tests: run `cd skills\tableau-migration; py -3.11 -m pytest tests -q` and keep it green
  (baseline 956 passed / 1 skipped / 1 xfailed). Report-schema changes are additive only ‚Äî never
  rename or remove existing report keys.
- Fractal mirror: after editing any `skills/<name>/` file, re-mirror it into
  `plugins/tableau-fabric-skills/skills/<name>/` with `robocopy /MIR` (excluding `__pycache__`,
  `.pytest_cache`, `*.pyc`) before committing.
- Secrets: never commit a real `.env`, a Tableau workbook/extract, a PAT, a Connected App secret,
  or a sidecar key. Only `.env.example` templates. See `SECURITY.md` and `.gitleaks.toml`.
- Clean room: `cyphou/Tableau-To-PowerBI` is reference-only ‚Äî copy nothing (its MIT license
  notwithstanding); `microsoft/skills-for-fabric` is a structure/convention model used with our
  own prose. Details in `CLEANROOM.md` and `AGENTS.md`.
- Commits: the user is the author; append
  `Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>`. Do not push unless asked.

## MCP

To exercise the landing zone from Cursor, add the deployed (or local) endpoint to
`~/.cursor/mcp.json` or `.cursor/mcp.json` with a `url` ending in `/mcp` and an `x-api-key`
header ‚Äî prefer `"${env:TABLEAU_MCP_API_KEY}"` over pasting the key. Full guide:
`skills/tableau-mcp-landing-zone/resources/mcp-clients.md`.
